description: We hosted our yearly gala online via facebook line. Information about the census was given to individuals that went ahead and attended it.

Shared a 56-second Census PSA to our Facebook page that was entirely in Vietnamese with a Vietnamese caption. The speaker in the video is a Vietnamese middle-aged man who is the Executive Producer of Dan Sinh Media, a Vietnamese network. He talked about different services and programs that Census data is used to to determine funding for.

A Humans of Census post about Michelle, who lives in Westminster, Orange County, and is the daughter of a cosmetologist. The caption explains how Michelle is the founder of a pop-up restaurant whos struggled financially since shelter-in-place limits her ability to booth at food festivals. It then explains that funding for SBA loans, which are available to small Vietnamese business owners like Michelle, is determined by Census data. A link to fill out a digital pledge card is included.
